[
    {
        "content": "<p>I have a bindgen issue, hope I can some help here. I add a C function as this in <code>include/linux/irqflags.h</code>, </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"C\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">static</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kr\">inline</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">void</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">local_interrupt_enable</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"kt\">void</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">          </span><span class=\"kt\">int</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">new_count</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">          </span><span class=\"n\">new_count</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hardirq_disable_exit</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">          </span><span class=\"k\">if</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">((</span><span class=\"n\">new_count</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">HARDIRQ_DISABLE_MASK</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">==</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                  </span><span class=\"kt\">unsigned</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">long</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">flags</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">                  </span><span class=\"n\">flags</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">raw_cpu_read</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">local_interrupt_disable_state</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">flags</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                  </span><span class=\"n\">local_irq_restore</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">flags</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                  </span><span class=\"cm\">/*</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">                   * TODO: re-read preempt count can be avoided, but it needs</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">                   * should_resched() taking another parameter as the current</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">                   * preempt count</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">                   */</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                  </span><span class=\"n\">preempt_check_resched</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"w\">          </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>and bindgen gives me an error:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Unable to generate bindings: clang diagnosed error: ../include/linux/irqflags.h:294:3: error: call to undeclared function 'preempt_check_resched'; ISO C99 and later do not support implicit function declarations [-Wimplicit-function-declaration]</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>because <code>preempt_check_resched()</code> is a C macro (defined in <code>include/linux/preempt.h</code> and I included it in <code>include/linux/irqflags.h</code>), and in this case <code>local_interrupt_enable()</code> is not supposed to be called by Rust code, so I don't want bindgen to generate binding for it at all. And yet, seems bindgen (or libclang) needs to parse function to some degree.</p>\n<p>My question is: is there a way to avoid this?</p>",
        "id": 497553017,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1738625887
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You could explicitly exclude the function by name?</p>",
